The original work — the Antigravity (`agy` / Gemini 3.5) companion for Claude Code,
including the command set, the Node companion runtime, agy log scanning, and the
test harness — is by Idun Labs and remains under the MIT License.

Modifications in this fork (dpa-plus), extending it toward codex-plugin-cc parity:

  - /antigravity:adversarial-review (red-team review)
  - opt-in stop-review-gate (Stop hook + ALLOW/BLOCK contract, fail-safe)
  - --model passthrough (capability-probed) and --wait
  - --json structured review output + ported review-output schema
  - logscan hardening for agy 1.0.8's benign pre-auth error window
  - empty-output-as-failure hardening

Adversarial-review and stop-review-gate prompts are adapted from OpenAI's
codex-plugin-cc (MIT). All changes remain under the MIT License.
